  "texts": [
    "Additionally, we conducted an experiment to verify the adequacy of our execution time measurement method.",
    "We calculated the standard deviation of 1000 measurements, where each measurement represented the execution time of a specific input using our method.",
    "The standard deviation was found to be negligible compared to the range of execution times observed in our case studies.Including the timestamp function's overhead posed another potential threat to the validity of execution time measurements.",
    "To address this, we designed an experiment to measure the overhead of the timestamp function itself.",
    "Our results showed that this overhead was negligible compared to the typical execution times recorded for our programs across different case studies.This study presents several opportunities for further research and development:• Tailored Algorithm Selection: Future endeavors should prioritize a strategic selection between GA and RL, underpinned by an understanding of the application's specific demands, operational constraints, and the criticality of precise WCET estimation."
